         * The easy case:  (|p|-1)/2  is odd, so 2 has an inverse
         * modulo  (|p|-1)/2,  and square roots can be computed
         * directly by modular eponentiation.
         * We have
         *     2 * (|p|+1)/4 == 1   (mod (|p|-1)/2),
         * so we can use eponent  (|p|+1)/4,  i.e.  (|p|-3)/4 + 1.
